    "@language" : "es",
    "@value" : "casa de cambio"
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "exchange bureau"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://ontologia.segittur.es/turismo/def/core#FinancialService"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://ontologia.segittur.es/turismo/def/core#Excursionist",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Person who travels but does not spend the night in a main destination other than their usual environment, for any main purpose other than to be employed by an entity resident in the country or place visited."
  }, {
    "@language" : "es",
    "@value" : "Persona que viaja pero no pernocta en un destino principal distinto al de su entorno habitual, con cualquier finalidad principal que no sea la de ser empleado por una entidad residente en el país o lugar visitado."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "excursionist"
  }, {
    "@language" : "es",
    "@value" : "excursionista"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://ontologia.segittur.es/turismo/def/core#PersonRole"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://ontologia.segittur.es/turismo/def/core#ExhibitionHall",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "es",
    "@value" : "Espacio de fomento, promoción y difusión de las artes plásticas."
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Space for the promotion, promotion and dissemination of the plastic arts."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "exhibition hall"
  }, {
    "@language" : "es",
    "@value" : "sala de exposiciones"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://ontologia.segittur.es/turismo/def/core#LeisureAndCultureFacility"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://ontologia.segittur.es/turismo/def/core#FarmSchool",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Educational and learning space where activities related to nature, the rural world and respect for the environment are carried out."
  }, {
    "@language" : "es",
    "@value" : "Espacio educativo y de aprendizaje donde se realizan actividades relacionadas con la naturaleza, el mundo rural y el respeto al medio ambiente."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "farm school"
  }, {
    "@language" : "es",
    "@value" : "granja escuela"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://ontologia.segittur.es/turismo/def/core#EducationalFacility"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://ontologia.segittur.es/turismo/def/core#Ferry",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "es",
    "@value" : "Barco que enlaza dos puntos llevando pasajeros y a veces vehículos en horarios programados. Forman parte del transporte público en algunas ciudades situadas en la costa, con bahías, grandes lagos o ríos, permitiendo el tránsito directo entre dos puntos y su coste es mucho menor a la construcción de puentes y túneles. En algunas regiones la palabra transbordador se usa para el buque que une distancias cortas (dos orillas de un río, por ejemplo), mientras que ferry se denomina a un buque que cubre mayores recorridos y es también de mayores dimensiones."
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Boat that connects two points carrying passengers and sometimes vehicles at scheduled times. They are part of public transport in some cities located on the coast, with bays, large lakes or rivers, allowing direct transit between two points and their cost is much lower than the construction of bridges and tunnels. In some regions the word ferry is used for a ship that connects short distances (two banks of a river, for example), while a ferry is a ship that covers longer distances and is also larger."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "ferry"
  }, {
